{"title_page": "Jean-Pierre Nsame", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}Giorgina \n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Jean-Pierre Nsame\n| fullname            = Jean-Pierre Nsame\n| image               = Jean-Pierre Nsame 2017 (cropped).jpg\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1993|5|1}}\n| birth_place         = [[Douala]], Cameroon\n| height              = {{height|m=1.88}}\n| position            = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Striker]]\n| currentclub         = [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]]\n| clubnumber          = 18\n| youthyears1         = 2008\u20132012 | youthclubs1 = [[Angers SCO|Angers]]\n| years1              = 2012\u20132016 | clubs1 = [[Angers SCO|Angers II]]              | caps1 = 38 | goals1 = 22\n| years2              = 2012\u20132016 | clubs2 = [[Angers SCO|Angers]]                 | caps2 = 23 | goals2 = 1\n| years3              = 2013\u20132014 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[USJA Carquefou|Carquefou]] (loan) | caps3 = 22 | goals3 = 0\n| years4              = 2014\u20132015 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[Amiens SC|Amiens]] (loan)         | caps4 = 34 | goals4 = 7\n| years5              = 2016\u20132017 | clubs5 = [[Servette FC|Servette]]              | caps5 = 31 | goals5 = 23\n| years6              = 2017\u2013     | clubs6 = [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]]         | caps6 = 83 | goals6 = 46\n| nationalyears1      = 2017\u2013\n| nationalteam1       = [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]]\n| nationalcaps1       = 1\n| nationalgoals1      = 0\n| club-update = 01:52, 14 January 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate    = 22:47, 5 November 2017 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Jean-Pierre Nsame''' (born 1 May 1993) is a Cameroonian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] and the [[Cameroon national football team]].\n\n==Club career==\nNsame made his professional debut in April 2012, in a 1\u20131 [[Ligue 2]] draw against [[FC Metz|Metz]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuille_match/75084|title=FC Metz vs. Angers SCO|publisher=[[Ligue de Football Professionnel|lfp.fr]]|language=French|date=27 April 2012|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Young Boys===\nIn July 2017 he joined Young Boys from second division side [[Servette FC]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mbuye |first1=Basil K |title=BSC Young Boys Sign Jean Pierre Nsame |url=https://sports24cameroon.com/bsc-young-boys-sign-jean-pierre-nsame/ |website=Sports24 Cameroon |accessdate=23 April 2019 |date=20 July 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423213118/https://sports24cameroon.com/bsc-young-boys-sign-jean-pierre-nsame/ |archive-date=23 April 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nIn 2017\u201318 he was part of the Young Boys squad that won the [[Swiss Super League]] for the first time in 32 years.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Homewood |first1=Brian |title=Soccer - Young Boys end 32-year wait for Swiss title and end Basel dominance |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-swiss/soccer-young-boys-end-32-year-wait-for-swiss-title-and-end-basel-dominance-idUKKBN1HZ0YS |accessdate=23 April 2019 |work=Reuters |date=28 April 2018}}</ref> He helped the club repeat as champions the following campaign, scoring 15 goals in 31 [[2018\u201319 Swiss Super League|league]] appearances.\n\nOn 14 September 2019, Nsame netted his first hat-trick for the club in a 11\u20132 victory over fifth division side [[FC Freienbach]] in the second round of the [[2019\u201320 Swiss Cup|Swiss Cup]]. Five days later, he scored his first goal in [[UEFA|European competition]] in a 1\u20132 defeat to Portuguese side [[FC Porto]] in the group stage of the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/fc-porto-vs-young-boys/420447|title=FC Porto 2-1 BSC Young Boys Bern|website=Sky Sports|date=19 September 2019|accessdate=14 January 2020}}</ref> On 24 November, he scored a hat-trick in a 4\u20133 win over [[FC Sion]] in the [[2019\u201320 Swiss Super League|Swiss Super League]]; the match also saw [[Pajtim Kasami]] score a hat-trick for Sion.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/sion-vs-young-boys/411111|title=FC Sion 3-4 BSC Young Boys Bern|website=Sky Sports|date=24 November 2019|accessdate=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nHe was called up to the [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] squad for the [[2017 Confederations Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mazibuko |first1=Sandile |title=Christian Bassogog tops Cameroon Confederation Cup squad |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/news/broos-includes-seven-new-faces-in-cameroons-confed-cup-squad/1dr2n0l819d3r1a74bmep6y3cj |website=Goal |accessdate=23 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe earned his first cap for Cameroon when he started their match against [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] on 4 September 2017 in a qualifying match for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=2018 World Cup: Cameroon fail to qualify after Nigeria draw |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41154779 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=23 April 2019 |date=4 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life== <ref>{{Cite web|title = Jean-Pierre Nsame (Angers) mis en examen pour violences sur son b\u00e9b\u00e9|url = https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Jean-pierre-nsame-angers-mis-en-examen-pour-violences-sur-son-bebe/607075|website = L'Equipe.fr|accessdate = 12 November 2015|language = fr-FR}}</ref>\n\nHis family name is correctly spelled ''Nsame'', not ''Nsam\u00e9''.<ref>https://www.blick.ch/sport/fussball/superleague/yb-star-nsame-ist-in-frankreich-angeklagt-es-zerreisst-mich-dass-ich-mein-kind-nicht-sehen-darf-id7400436.html</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 15 December 2019}}<ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{cite web|url=https://us.soccerway.com/players/jean-pierre-nsame/241557/|title=J. NSAM\u00c9|website=Soccerway|accessdate=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text