{"title_page": "Brahim Hemdani", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Brahim Hemdani\n| fullname = Ibrahim Hemdani\n| image = Brahim Hemdani, Nou Camp.JPG\n| image_size = 180\n| caption = Hemdani playing for [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] in November 2007\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1978|3|15|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Colombes]], France\n| height = 1.80 m\n| position = [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|Defensive midfielder]]\n| youthclubs1 = [[Racing Club de France football Colombes 92|Racing Paris]]\n| youthyears1 = 1996\u20131997\n| years1 = 1997\u20131998\n| clubs1 = [[AS Cannes|Cannes]]\n| caps1 = 27\n| goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 1998\u20132001\n| clubs2 = [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]]\n| caps2 = 53\n| goals2 = 3\n| years3 = 2001\u20132005\n| clubs3 = [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]]\n| caps3 = 95\n| goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2005\u20132009\n| clubs4 = [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]\n| caps4 = 67\n| goals4 = 2\n| totalcaps = 242\n| totalgoals = 7\n| nationalyears1 = 2008\u20132009\n| nationalteam1 = [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n\n'''Brahim Hemdani''' (born 15 March 1978) is a Algerian former professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\nHemdani was born in [[Colombes]], [[Hauts-de-Seine]]. He started his career with [[AS Cannes|Cannes]], where he spent two seasons. He later transferred to [[RC Strasbourg Alsace]], spending three seasons with the club. He then joined [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]], which he helped reach the [[UEFA Cup]] final in [[2004 UEFA Cup Final|2004]].\n\nHemdani then joined Rangers on 14 June 2005 on a [[Bosman transfer]] and signed a four-year contract.<ref name=\"Rangers transfer\">{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/r/rangers/4090958.stm | publisher=BBC Sport website | title=Rangers clinch deal for Hemdani | date=14 June 2005}}</ref> He suffered from injury problems during his first season, waiting until late October to make his debut against [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]].<ref name=\"Dundee Utd 0-0 Rangers \">{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/4338832.stm | publisher=BBC Sport website | title=Dundee Utd 0-0 Rangers | date=16 October 2005}}</ref> Hemdani was a regular in the side from then on and helped the club reach the last 16 of the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] for the first time in their history. The season ended with the side finishing third in the league and trophyless. The following summer, [[Paul Le Guen]] took over as manager and Hemdani began the [[2006\u201307 in Scottish football|2006\u201307]] season in [[midfielder|midfield]] but was moved to the [[defender (association football)|centre of defence]].\n\nHemdani scored his first goal for Rangers midway through that season, a shot from outside the box to equalise in the 88th minute of an [[Old Firm]] game on 17 December 2006.<ref name=\"Rangers 1-1 Celtic\">{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/6177705.stm | publisher=BBC Sport| title=Rangers 1-1 Celtic | date=17 December 2006}}</ref> His second goal came in similar circumstances in a [[2006\u201307 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]] match in March 2007, against [[CA Osasuna]], scoring to equalise in injury time.<ref name=\"Rangers 1-1 Osasuna \">{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/europe/6415057.stm | publisher=BBC Sport| title=Rangers 1-1 Osasuna | date=8 March 2007}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 April 2007, Hemdani was named Rangers Player of the Year at an award ceremony, voted for by the club's fans.<ref name=\"Player of the Year\">{{cite news|url=http://www.rangers.premiumtv.co.uk/page/Headlines/0,,5~1011888,00.html |title=Hemdani Named Player Of The Year |publisher=Rangers official website |date=16 April 2007 }}{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He made his 100th appearance for [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] on 13 March 2008 in a [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]] match against [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]],<ref name=\"Hemdani 100\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/europe/7285148.stm|title=W Bremen 1-0 Rangers (agg 1-2) |publisher=BBC Sport|date=13 March 2008}}</ref> the club went on to reach [[2008 UEFA Cup Final|the final that season]], which Hemdani played the full 90 minutes of. However, this turned out to be his last match for Rangers as the [[2008\u201309 Rangers F.C. season|2008\u201309 season]] saw Hemdani frozen out of the first team. He left on 1 June 2009 having made a total of 108 appearances and scoring twice.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/r/rangers/8077300.stm|title=Weir poised for new Rangers deal |date=1 June 2009|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nHemdani declined the chance to be included as part of the Algeria national squad on several occasions in the past.<ref name=\"Players reject Algeria\">{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/africa/3570178.stm| title=Players reject Algeria\n| publisher=BBC Sport website| date=16 August 2004}}</ref> However, in February 2008 he had a change of heart and decided to play for [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]].<ref name=\"Brahim Hemdani Has World Cup Dream With Algeria\">{{cite news | url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football-news/2008/02/08/brahim-hemdani-has-world-cup-dream-with-algeria-86908-20312646/| title=Brahim Hemdani Has World Cup Dream With Algeria\n| publisher=Daily Record| date=8 February 2008}}</ref> Hemdani made his [[Algeria national football team|Algerian]] debut in a [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification|2010 World Cup qualifier]] against [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] on 31 May 2008.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/africa/7429606.stm \"Senegal 1-0 Algeria\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419122641/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/africa/7429606.stm |date=19 April 2012 }} BBC Sport website (31 May 200)8</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHemdani's family are originally from [[Larba\u00e2 Nath Irathen]], near [[Tizi Ouzou]], in the [[Kabylie]] region of [[Algeria]] and he spends a significant amount of time there every year.\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n:Sources:<ref>{{{{FootballDatabase.eu|206|accessdate=22 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{NFT|26083|accessdate=22 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup<ref group=\"lower-alpha\">Includes [[Coupe de France]], [[Coupe de la Ligue]], [[Scottish League Cup]] and [[Scottish Cup]]</ref>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[AS Cannes|Cannes]]\n|[[1997\u201398 French Division 1|1997\u201398]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[French Division 1|Division 1]]\n|20||1||4||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||24||1\n|-\n|[[1998\u201399 French Division 2|1998\u201399]]\n|7||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||7||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!27!!1!!4!!0!!colspan=2|\u2014!!colspan=2|\u2014!!31!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[RC Strasbourg|Strasbourg]]\n|[[1998\u201399 French Division 1|1998\u201399]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Division 1\n|12||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||12||0\n|-\n|[[1999\u20132000 French Division 1|1999\u201300]]\n|29||3||7||1||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||36||4\n|-\n|[[2000\u201301 French Division 1|2000\u201301]]\n|12||0||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||13||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!53!!3!!8!!1!!colspan=2|\u2014!!colspan=2|\u2014!!61!!4\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]]\n|[[2000\u201301 Olympique de Marseille season|2000\u201301]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Division 1\