{"title_page": "Jose Paulo Dias", "text_new": "{{short description|Olympic sailor from Brazil}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = Jos\u00e9 Paulo Dias<ref name=\"Sports-Reference\" />\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| native_name    = \n| birth_name     =  \n| fullname       = \n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{BRA}}\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1957|12|23|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = \n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{convert|1.78|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = \n| classes        = [[Soling]]\n| club           = \n| collegeteam    = \n| coach          = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = 27 February 2020\n}}\n\n'''Jos\u00e9 Paulo Dias''' is a sailor from [[Brazil]], who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1988 Summer Olympics]] in [[Busan]], [[South Korea]] as helmsman in the [[Soling]]. With crew members [[Jose Augusto Dias]], [[Daniel Adler (sailor)|Daniel Adler]] and [[Christoph Bergman]] they took the 5th place.<ref name=\"OS1988\" /> Jos\u00e9 Paulo with crew members [[Jose Augusto Dias]] and [[Daniel Adler (sailor)|Daniel Adler]] took 13th place during the [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]] as helmsman in the [[Soling]].<ref name=\"OS1992\" />\n{{Footer South American Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer Brazilian Championship Winners in Soling}}\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n  <ref name = Sports-Reference>{{cite web\n                                  |url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20121217080004/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/di/jose-paulo-dias-1.html\n                                  |title      = Jos\u00e9 Paulo Dias Bio, Stats, and Results \n                                  |publisher  = Sports-Reference.com \n                                  |work       = Olym